A **home loan refinance calculator** helps you decide if switching lenders is worthwhile. It calculates the monthly saving from a lower rate, the total interest saved over your remaining loan term, and the break-even period — the number of months it takes for your savings to recoup the cost of refinancing.

Refinancing a $480,000 loan from 6.8% to 6.1% (with $2,500 in costs) saves approximately **$171 per month** and breaks even in just 14 months. If you plan to hold the loan for more than 2 years, refinancing typically makes financial sense — even after factoring in all costs.
